nodes.bodyText:
I'd suggest defining a static LOG at the top of the class like (this is how it is used elsewhere in Amplify):
private static final Logger LOG = Amplify.Logging.forNamespace("amplify:devmenu");

Then reference it like this:
LOG.warn("Error reading...");

warn is probably more appropriate than error since there is no RuntimeException being thrown.

